Using Mysql:

creating a user in mysql:
CREATE USER YOUR-USERNAME-HERE@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY YOUR-PASSWORD-HERE;
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON my_database.* TO 'meow'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;


Granting perms to user:
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON posty_post_data.* TO YOUR-USERNMAE-HERE@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

dumping sql data (exporting)
mysqldump -u YOUR-USERNAME-HERE -p posty_post_data > posty_post_data.sql

importing sql data (importing)
	> log in from terminal << mysql -u YOUR-USERNAME-HERE -p >>
		> create a target db << CREATE DATABASE your_database; >>
		> EXIT;
	> import the sql file to target db << mysql -u USERNAME-HERE -p your_database < /path/to/your/file.sql >>






